commit.message:
allow to get the git version without having a (python) package

  $ setuptools-git-version
  1.0.4.1+78f88be

Merge pull request #5 from pyfidelity/version-injection

Version injection

allow to build a package using a git-based version without modifying it upfront

instead of:

  $ python setup.py sdist […]

one can now use:

  $ python -m setuptools_git_version sdist […]

the resulting package may then be uploaded to devpi for example:

  $ devpi upload dist/…
rename module to avoid conflicts when installed via `pip`
bump version & apply change log cosmetics
we still use manual versions here :-)

Merge pull request #1 from tomster/python3-compat

always decode result from check_output

always decode result from check_output

in python 3.4 the result is of type ``byte``, so we must explicitly
convert this. it seems to work well enough in python2.7 but short of
setting up mock tests for check_output i couldn't come up with a test
for this.
make sure we work with python3, too :)
it seems we need a non-alpha release to make this work on a daily basis... :)
the first `setuptools` version working with '+' versions seems to be 8.0
